==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Livelihood
<hw>Live"li*hood</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>livelode</ets>, <ets>liflode</ets>, prop., course of life, life's
support, maintenance, fr. AS. <ets>l⟦imac⟧f</ets> life +
<ets>l⟦amac⟧d</ets> road, way, maintenance. Confused with
<ets>livelihood</ets> liveliness. See <er>Life</er>, and
<er>Lode</er>.]</ety> <def>Subsistence or living, as dependent on some
means of support; the means for support of life; maintenance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The opportunities of gaining an honest <qex>livelihood</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is their profession and <qex>livelihood</qex> to get their
living by practices for which they deserve to forfeit their lives.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Livelihood</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Livelihood
<hw>Live"li*hood</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lively</ets> +
<ets>-hood</ets>.]</ety> <def>Liveliness; appearance of life.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Livelily</ent>⟦br⟧
